<subSubSection id="DEEF5AB8C101FFE826F6F42F78F7FC57" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="964A0933C101FFE826F6F42F78F7FC57" blockId="1.[151,1437,473,998]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">
Notes. This species was described by de Joannis (1929) on the basis of a single female specimen from Cho Ganh (Vietnam). 
<bibRefCitation id="F26474C2C101FFE826BCF40A780EFDCF" author="Toth, B." box="[221,351,614,638]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" pagination="437 - 442" refId="ref3604" refString="Toth, B. (2019) Notes on the species of Naarda Walker, 1866 (Lepidoptera: Erebidae, Hypeninae) from mainland China, with the description of a new species and establishment of a new synonymy. Journal of Asia-Pacific Entomology, 22, 437 - 442. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. aspen. 2019.02.004" type="journal article" year="2019">Tóth (2019)</bibRefCitation>
evaluated the relationship between this taxon and 
<taxonomicName id="51F572B0C101FFE825EAF40B7DC0FDCF" authority="Sugi, 1982" authorityName="Sugi" authorityYear="1982" box="[907,1169,614,638]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Naarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pectinata">
<emphasis id="A481D521C101FFE825EAF40B7D5EFDCF" box="[907,1039,615,638]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">N. pectinata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="F26474C2C101FFE82279F40A7DC0FDCF" author="Sugi, S." box="[1048,1169,614,638]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" pagination="355 - 380" refId="ref3463" refString="Sugi, S. (1982) Noctuidae (excluding Herminiinae). In: Inoue, H., Sugi, S., Kuroko, H., Moriuti, S., Kawabe, A. &amp; Owada, M. (Eds.), Moths of Japan. Vols. 1 - 2. Kodansha, Tokyo, pp. 669 - 913 &amp; pp. 334 - 405, pls. 37 + 164 - 223 + 229 + 278 + 355 - 380." type="journal article" year="1982">Sugi, 1982</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, synonymized these two and recorded 
<collectingCountry id="EEE249A3C101FFE82749F4E67827FD13" box="[296,374,650,674]" name="Taiwan" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
and N. 
<collectingCountry id="EEE249A3C101FFE827AAF4E67B5AFD13" box="[459,523,650,674]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">China</collectingCountry>
as the newly recorded locality of 
<taxonomicName id="51F572B0C101FFE82514F4E77D5DFD13" authorityName="de Joannis" authorityYear="1929" box="[885,1036,650,674]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Naarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="postpallida">
<emphasis id="A481D521C101FFE82514F4E77D5DFD13" box="[885,1036,650,674]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">N. postpallida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In the same article, the author stated “The [examined] female specimens showed no difference from the 
<typeStatus id="494EB791C101FFE82502F4C27A91FD77" box="[867,960,686,710]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="51F572B0C101FFE82582F4C37D2BFD77" authorityName="de Joannis" authorityYear="1929" box="[995,1146,686,710]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Naarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="postpallida">
<emphasis id="A481D521C101FFE82582F4C37D2BFD77" box="[995,1146,686,710]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">N. postpallida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in external appearance and the [examined] males cannot be distinguished from the type material of 
<taxonomicName id="51F572B0C101FFE825C2F4BF7D77FD5B" authorityName="Sugi" authorityYear="1982" box="[931,1062,723,746]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Naarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pectinata">
<emphasis id="A481D521C101FFE825C2F4BF7D77FD5B" box="[931,1062,723,746]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">N. pectinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
neither by external, nor by genital characters (p. 438)”, however, the illustrated male 
<typeStatus id="494EB791C101FFE824CEF49B7A5AFCBE" box="[687,779,759,783]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">paratype</typeStatus>
genitalia of 
<taxonomicName id="51F572B0C101FFE825EEF49B7D41FCBF" authorityName="Sugi" authorityYear="1982" box="[911,1040,759,782]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Naarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pectinata">
<emphasis id="A481D521C101FFE825EEF49B7D41FCBF" box="[911,1040,759,782]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">N. pectinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="F26474C2C101FFE82253F49A7DFAFCBF" author="Sugi, S." box="[1074,1195,758,782]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" pagination="355 - 380" refId="ref3463" refString="Sugi, S. (1982) Noctuidae (excluding Herminiinae). In: Inoue, H., Sugi, S., Kuroko, H., Moriuti, S., Kawabe, A. &amp; Owada, M. (Eds.), Moths of Japan. Vols. 1 - 2. Kodansha, Tokyo, pp. 669 - 913 &amp; pp. 334 - 405, pls. 37 + 164 - 223 + 229 + 278 + 355 - 380." type="journal article" year="1982">Sugi (1982</bibRefCitation>
: pl. 379: 7) differ from that of Tóth’s illustrated Vietnamese and Taiwanese specimens by asymmetrical costal process of valva with right one rod-like with parallel lateral margins and left one broader than left one rather than symmetrical, tapering toward apex. Besides, 
<bibRefCitation id="F26474C2C101FFE82696F50E7824FCCB" author="Sugi, S." box="[247,373,866,890]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" pagination="355 - 380" refId="ref3463" refString="Sugi, S. (1982) Noctuidae (excluding Herminiinae). In: Inoue, H., Sugi, S., Kuroko, H., Moriuti, S., Kawabe, A. &amp; Owada, M. (Eds.), Moths of Japan. Vols. 1 - 2. Kodansha, Tokyo, pp. 669 - 913 &amp; pp. 334 - 405, pls. 37 + 164 - 223 + 229 + 278 + 355 - 380." type="journal article" year="1982">Sugi (1982)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="51F572B0C101FFE82786F50F7B38FCCB" authorityName="Sugi" authorityYear="1982" box="[487,617,867,890]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Naarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pectinata">
<emphasis id="A481D521C101FFE82786F50F7B38FCCB" box="[487,617,867,890]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">N. pectinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the basis of 
<specimenCount id="80F3C2BAC101FFE8256FF50E7A07FCCB" box="[782,854,866,890]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" type="male">5 male</specimenCount>
specimens, one additional male specimen is illustrated in 
<bibRefCitation id="F26474C2C101FFE826D0F5EA781BFC2F" author="Kishida, Y." box="[177,330,902,926]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" pagination="207 - 214" refId="ref3394" refString="Kishida, Y. (2011) Hypeninae. In: Kishida, Y. (Ed.), The Standard of Moths in Japan 2. Gakken Education Publishing, Tokyo, pp. 207 - 214, pls. 37 - 39. [in Japanese]" type="book chapter" year="2011">Kishida (2011</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="F26474C2C101FFE82732F5EA78DBFC2F" author="Kishida, Y." box="[339,394,902,926]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" refId="ref3444" refString="Kishida, Y. (2020) The Moths in Japan. Gakken, Tokyo, 200 pp." type="book" year="2020">2020</bibRefCitation>
) and so far no female specimen of this taxon is available for comparing with 
<bibRefCitation id="F26474C2C101FFE822D2F5EA7C12FC2F" author="Toth, B." box="[1203,1347,902,926]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" pagination="437 - 442" refId="ref3604" refString="Toth, B. (2019) Notes on the species of Naarda Walker, 1866 (Lepidoptera: Erebidae, Hypeninae) from mainland China, with the description of a new species and establishment of a new synonymy. Journal of Asia-Pacific Entomology, 22, 437 - 442. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. aspen. 2019.02.004" type="journal article" year="2019">Tóth’s (2019)</bibRefCitation>
females from 
<collectingCountry id="EEE249A3C101FFE826B3F5C6787EFC73" box="[210,303,938,962]" name="Vietnam" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="EEE249A3C101FFE8275BF5C678D9FC73" box="[314,392,938,962]" name="Taiwan" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
and N. 
<collectingCountry id="EEE249A3C101FFE827BEF5C67B73FC73" box="[479,546,938,962]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">China</collectingCountry>
. According to the mentioned information, we revive 
<taxonomicName id="51F572B0C101FFE8223CF5C77C0AFC73" authority="Sugi, 1982" authorityName="Sugi" authorityYear="1982" box="[1117,1371,938,962]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Naarda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pectinata">
<emphasis id="A481D521C101FFE8223CF5C77DB1FC73" box="[1117,1248,939,962]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">N. pectinata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="F26474C2C101FFE82286F5C67C0AFC73" author="Sugi, S." box="[1255,1371,938,962]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" pagination="355 - 380" refId="ref3463" refString="Sugi, S. (1982) Noctuidae (excluding Herminiinae). In: Inoue, H., Sugi, S., Kuroko, H., Moriuti, S., Kawabe, A. &amp; Owada, M. (Eds.), Moths of Japan. Vols. 1 - 2. Kodansha, Tokyo, pp. 669 - 913 &amp; pp. 334 - 405, pls. 37 + 164 - 223 + 229 + 278 + 355 - 380." type="journal article" year="1982">Sugi, 1982</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis id="A481D521C101FFE8230DF5C67990FC57" bold="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">stat. rev.</emphasis>
) in the present study.
</paragraph>
